{
  "local_port": 37174,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What developed countries are vegetarian friendly?",
  "response": "Several developed countries are known for being vegetarian-friendly, offering a wide range of vegetarian options, restaurants, and policies that cater to those who follow plant-based diets. Here are some of the most vegetarian-friendly developed countries:\n\n### 1. **United Kingdom**\n   - **Why it\u2019s vegetarian-friendly**: The UK has a strong vegetarian and vegan culture, with many restaurants offering dedicated vegetarian menus. Supermarkets stock a wide variety of plant-based products.\n   - **Notable cities**: London, Bristol, Manchester.\n\n### 2. **Germany**\n   - **Why it\u2019s vegetarian-friendly**: Germany is home to a growing vegetarian and vegan movement, with many vegetarian restaurants and a strong emphasis on plant-based products. The country is also known for its vegetarian versions of traditional dishes.\n   - **Notable cities**: Berlin, Munich, Hamburg.\n\n### 3. **United States**\n   - **Why it\u2019s vegetarian-friendly**: The U.S. has a diverse food culture, with many vegetarian and vegan restaurants, especially in urban areas. The availability of plant-based products is widespread, and there is a growing awareness of vegetarianism.\n   - **Notable cities**: Los Angeles, New York, San Francisco.\n\n### 4. **Canada**\n   - **Why it\u2019s vegetarian-friendly**: Canada offers a variety of vegetarian options, particularly in urban centers. The country has a strong focus on health and wellness, which includes vegetarian and vegan diets.\n   - **Notable cities**: Toronto, Vancouver, Montreal.\n\n### 5. **Australia**\n   - **Why it\u2019s vegetarian-friendly**: Australia has a growing vegetarian and vegan scene, with many restaurants and cafes offering plant-based options. The country also has a strong focus on fresh, local produce.\n   - **Notable cities**: Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane.\n\n### 6. **Sweden**\n   - **Why it\u2019s vegetarian-friendly**: Sweden is known for its progressive food policies and has a growing number of vegetarian and vegan restaurants. The country also has a strong emphasis on sustainability, which aligns well with vegetarian diets.\n   - **Notable cities**: Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malm\u00f6.\n\n### 7. **Netherlands**\n   - **Why it\u2019s vegetarian-friendly**: The Netherlands has a strong vegetarian and vegan culture, with many restaurants offering plant-based options. The country is also known for its innovative food products, including plant-based meats.\n   - **Notable cities**: Amsterdam, Utrecht, Rotterdam.\n\n### 8. **New Zealand**\n   - **Why it\u2019s vegetarian-friendly**: New Zealand offers a variety of vegetarian options, particularly in urban areas. The country is also known for its focus on fresh, local produce and healthy eating.\n   - **Notable cities**: Auckland, Wellington, Christchurch.\n\n### 9. **Israel**\n   - **Why it\u2019s vegetarian-friendly**: Israel has a strong tradition of vegetarian cuisine, particularly in the form of Middle Eastern dishes like falafel, hummus, and tabbouleh. Many restaurants offer vegetarian and vegan options.\n   - **Notable cities**: Tel Aviv, Jerusalem, Haifa.\n\n### 10. **Japan**\n   - **Why it\u2019s vegetarian-friendly**: While traditional Japanese cuisine includes a lot of seafood, there is a growing number of vegetarian and vegan restaurants, especially in urban areas. Many traditional dishes can also be adapted to be vegetarian.\n   - **Notable cities**: Tokyo, Kyoto, Osaka.\n\n### 11. **Italy**\n   - **Why it\u2019s vegetarian-friendly**: Italian cuisine offers a variety of vegetarian options, including pasta dishes, pizzas, and risottos. Many Italian restaurants are accommodating to vegetarians.\n   - **Notable cities**: Rome, Florence, Milan.\n\n### 12. **France**\n   - **Why it\u2019s vegetarian-friendly**: While traditionally meat-heavy, France has seen a rise in vegetarian and vegan restaurants, particularly in urban areas. Many traditional dishes can be adapted to be vegetarian.\n   - **Notable cities**: Paris, Lyon, Bordeaux.\n\n### 13. **Switzerland**\n   - **Why it\u2019s vegetarian-friendly**: Switzerland offers a variety of vegetarian options, particularly in cities. The country is also known for its high-quality produce and innovative food products.\n   - **Notable cities**: Zurich, Geneva, Basel.\n\nThese countries have embraced vegetarianism in various ways, making it easier for vegetarians to find suitable food options and enjoy a diverse culinary experience.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
